  "title": "A Strange Visitor",
  "summary": "On Residential Avenue in Capital City on Etti IV, a yellow Labrador named Duke slips out of his home and is coaxed over by a loitering stranger, Giles Vermillion, who feeds him a sandwich and reads his collar to learn his owner is Simone Drake. Vermillion follows the dog to Simone's house and presses her intercom, claiming to be a friend of the absent Xegid and demanding to be let inside. Cautious in the wake of recent events, Simone refuses to open her door, and a prickly exchange ensues in which she informs him that Xegid was kidnapped by the rogue Wookiee and taken off-planet by the New Republic, with efforts underway to recover him. Vermillion grows alternately angry, smug, and flirtatious, but Simone rebuffs his every overture and finally orders him off her stoop. He departs with a sardonic remark about Xegid's friends, watched coldly by Duke, while the waitress Chantinelle, passing by, idly tries to question him before tossing the dog a treat and heading back to the embassy.",
